HEADWORD: Enrollment
<hw>En*roll"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>enr⟦ocir⟧lement</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>enrolment</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of enrolling;
registration.</def> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A writing in which anything is enrolled; a register;
a record.</def> <rj><au>Sir J. Davies.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

